Dani Shapiro is an American writer. Family History is written by Dani Shapiro. Family History is a novel written in 2003. Dani Shapiro created a podcast called Family Secrets. [BG] Boston is an American city.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Dani Shapiro was born in Boston.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Novel(x) ::: x is a novel.
Podcast(x) ::: x is a podcast.
BornIn(x, y) ::: x is born in y.
American(x) ::: x is an American.
Book(x) ::: x is a book.
WrittenBy(x, y) ::: x is written by y.
NovelWriter(x) ::: x is a novel writer.
AmericanWriter(x) ::: x is an American writer.
Created(x, y) ::: x created y.
AmericanCity(x) ::: x is an American city.
Premises:
¬Novel(familySecrets) ∧ Podcast(familySecrets) ::: A podcast is not a novel.
∀x (BornIn(x, y) → American(x)) ::: If a person is born in American City, the person is American.
∀x ∀y ((Book(x) ∧ Novel(x) ∧ WrittenBy(x, y)) → NovelWriter(y)) ::: If a book is novel and it is written by a person, then the person is a novel writer.
AmericanWriter(dani) ::: Dani Shapiro is an American writer.
Book(familyHistory) ∧ WrittenBy(familyHistory, dani) ::: Family History is written by Dani Shapiro.
Book(familyHistory) ∧ Novel(familyHistory) ::: Family History is a novel written in 2003.
Created(dani, familySecrets) ::: Dani Shapiro created a podcast called Family Secrets.
AmericanCity(boston) ::: Boston is an American city.
Conclusion:
BornIn(dani, boston) ::: Dani Shapiro was born in Boston.
